Threat Identification
1. Insider Threat
Description

A security risk caused by employees or authorized users misusing their access.

Possible Impact
Data theft
Information leakage
Financial loss
Prevention
Access control
Employee monitoring
Security awareness training
2. Malware
Description

Malicious software designed to damage or disrupt systems.

Possible Impact
Data loss
System crashes
Ransomware attacks
Prevention
Antivirus software
Software updates
Safe browsing
3. Phishing
Description

Fraudulent emails or websites that trick users into revealing sensitive information.

Possible Impact
Account compromise
Financial fraud
Identity theft
Prevention
Verify email senders
Avoid suspicious links
User awareness training
4. Weak Passwords
Description

Simple or reused passwords that are easy for attackers to guess.

Possible Impact
Unauthorized access
Data theft
Prevention
Strong passwords
Password managers
Multi-Factor Authentication
5. Unpatched Systems
Description

Systems without the latest security updates.

Possible Impact
Malware infections
Exploitation of vulnerabilities
Prevention
Regular updates
Patch management
Vulnerability scanning